      "content": "i get what you're saying about science, but i've seen people talk about how infrasound can cause anxiety or even hallucinations. if they were layering those frequencies underneath a stream, even if it's \"purposely\" subtle, wouldn't it be a perfect way to do it without leaving a trace? like, how would anyone even prove it's happening if the frequencies are just below the threshold of being able to consciously identify them?",
